### 3. No Security Headers (OWASP A05: Security Misconfiguration)

Express sends no security-relevant HTTP headers by default, leaving the app open to clickjacking, MIME sniffing, and XSS via reflected content.

**Fix:** Add `helmet` (sets ~14 protective headers in one line):

```js
const helmet = require('helmet');
app.use(helmet());
```

This enables `Content-Security-Policy`, `X-Frame-Options`, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`, and others automatically.

